🔹 Types of Sequential Circuits
1️⃣ Synchronous

Controlled by clock signal

Changes occur at clock edge

2️⃣ Asynchronous

No clock

Output changes immediately

📌 GATE mostly focuses on synchronous circuits

🔹 Flip-Flops (Memory Elements)

Flip-flops store 1 bit of data.

🔹 SR Flip-Flop

Inputs:

S (Set)

R (Reset)

S	R	Q(next)
0	0	No change
0	1	0
1	0	1
1	1	Invalid ❌

📌 GATE Trap: S=R=1 is invalid.

🔹 JK Flip-Flop

Improved version of SR.

J	K	Q(next)
0	0	No change
0	1	0
1	0	1
1	1	Toggle

📌 No invalid state.

